	<exercisegroup><title> <em>Solve by Hand</em> </title>
	
		<introduction>
			<p>
				Workout the following problems on paper then enter your answers in the corresponding boxes.
			</p>
		</introduction>

		<exercise label="c2-cr-ww-01"><title> <em>Give the Separable Form</em> </title>

			<introduction>
				<p>
					Write each differential equation in the separable form
					<me>
						\frac{dy}{dx} = f(x)\cdot g(y)
					</me>.
				</p>
				<p>
					<em>Type your answer for <m>f(x)</m> into the left box and <m>g(y)</m> into the right box.</em>
				</p>
			</introduction>
				
			<webwork xml:id="c2-cr-ww-01-id">

				<description>
					Show a differential equation is separable.
				</description>
		
				<pg-code>
					Context()->variables->add(y => 'Real');
					$f1 = Formula("1 + cos(x)");
					$g1 = Formula("y");
					$f2 = Formula("1/x^2");
					$g2 = Formula("1 - y");
					$f3 = Formula("e^(x)/x");
					$g3 = Formula("(y^2 - 1)/y");
				</pg-code>
		
				<statement>
					
					<ol cols="2">
						<li>
							<p>
								<m>\displaystyle \frac{dy}{dx} - y\cos(x) = y </m>
							</p>

							<p>
								<m>\displaystyle \frac{dy}{dx} = </m>
								<var name="$f1" width="10" />
								<var name="$g1" width="10" />
							</p>
						</li>
						<li>
							<p>
								<m>\displaystyle x^2y + x^4\frac{dy}{dx} = x^2 </m>
							</p>

							<p>
								<m>\displaystyle \frac{dy}{dx} = </m>
								<var name="$f2" width="10" />
								<var name="$g2" width="10" />
							</p>
						</li>
						<li>
							<p>
								<m>\displaystyle xy\frac{dy}{dx} = e^xy^2 - e^x </m>
							</p>

							<p>
								<m>\displaystyle \frac{dy}{dx} = </m>
								<var name="$f3" width="10" />
								<var name="$g3" width="10" />
							</p>
						</li>
					</ol>

				</statement>
				
			</webwork>

			<solution>
				<ol>
					<li>
						<p>
							Move the <m> y\cos x </m> term to the right and factor out <m>y</m>.
							<md>
								<mrow>	\frac{dy}{dx}	\amp =	y + y\cos(x)	</mrow>
								<mrow>	\frac{dy}{dx}	\amp =	\ub{(1 + \cos(x))}_{f(x)}\us{g(y)}{\us{\uparrow}{\ul{y}}}	</mrow>
							</md>
						</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<p>
							Isolate the derivative and group the terms as shown below.
							<md>
								<mrow>	\frac{dy}{dx}	\amp =	\frac{1}{x^2} - \frac{y}{x^2} \quad\leftarrow \text{common factor: } \frac{1}{x^2}	</mrow>
								<mrow>	\frac{dy}{dx}	\amp =	\us{f(x)}{\us{\uparrow}{\ul{\frac{1}{x^2}}}} \cdot\ub{(1 - y)}_{g(y)}				</mrow>
							</md>
						</p>
					</li>
					<li>
						<p>
							We isolate the derivative and group the terms as shown below.
							<md>
								<mrow>	xy\frac{dy}{dx}	\amp =	e^xy^2 - e^x																									</mrow>
								<mrow>	\frac{dy}{dx}	\amp =	\frac{e^xy^2 - e^x}{xy}	\quad\leftarrow \text{common factor: } e^x												</mrow>
								<mrow>	\frac{dy}{dx}	\amp =	\frac{e^x \cdot (y^2 - 1)}{x \cdot y} \quad\leftarrow \left(\frac{AB}{CD} = \frac{A}{C}\cdot \frac{B}{D}\right)	</mrow>
								<mrow>	\frac{dy}{dx}	\amp =	\us{f(x)}{\us{\uparrow}{\ul{\frac{e^x}{x}}}} \cdot	\ub{\frac{y^2 - 1}{y}}_{g(y)}								</mrow>
							</md>.
						</p>
					</li>
				</ol>
				
			</solution>

		</exercise>

		<exercise label="c2-cr-ww-02"><title> <em>Solve the Differential Equation</em> </title>

			<introduction>
				<p>
					Complete each step below to solve the differential equation
					<me> \frac{dy}{dx} - y\cos(x) = y.</me>
					These are the same steps used in this chapter's examples. 
				</p>
			</introduction>
				
			<webwork xml:id="c2-cr-ww-02-id"> 
				<description>
					Solve a separable DE using separation of variables.
				</description>

				<pg-code>
					Context()->variables->add(y => 'Real');
					Context()->variables->add(c => 'Real');
					$ans1a = 1;
					$ans1b = Formula("1+cos(x)");
					$ans1c = Formula("y");
					$ans2a = Formula("1+cos(x)");
					$ans2b = Formula("1/y");
					$ans3a = Formula("x+sin(x)");
					$ans3b = Formula("ln|y|");
					$ans = Formula("c*e^(x+sin(x))");
				</pg-code>

				<statement>
					<p>
						<xref ref="sov-step-1" text="title" />. Give the order and separable form:
					</p>

					<p>
						<tabular>
							<col halign="right" />
							<row>
								<cell><m>\text{order:}</m></cell>
								<cell><var name="$ans1a"  width="5" /></cell>
								<cell></cell>
								<cell><m>\displaystyle \frac{dy}{dx} = </m></cell>
								<cell><var name="$ans1b" width="10" /></cell>
								<cell><var name="$ans1c" width="10" /></cell>
								<cell><m>\quad\qquad\leftarrow\text{ separable form}</m></cell>
							</row>
							<row>
								<cell><m>\phantom{\text{order:}}</m></cell>
								<cell></cell>
								<cell></cell>
								<cell><m>\phantom{\displaystyle \frac{dy}{dx} = }</m></cell>
								<cell><m>\overline{\overset{\uparrow}{f(x)}}</m></cell>
								<cell><m>\overline{\overset{\uparrow}{g(y)}}</m></cell>
								<cell></cell>
							</row>
						</tabular>
					</p>

					<p>
						<xref ref="sov-step-2" text="title" />. Divide both sides of the separable form by <m>g(y)</m> and apply the integral to both sides:
					</p>

					<p>
						<tabular halign="center">
							<row>
								<cell><m>\displaystyle\int</m></cell>
								<cell><var name="$ans2b" width="10" /></cell>
								<cell><m>\displaystyle dy = \int </m></cell>
								<cell><var name="$ans2a" width="10" /></cell>
								<cell><m>dx</m></cell>
							</row>
						</tabular>
					</p>

					<p>
						Now, compute the integrals (we have provided the constants):
					</p>

					<p>
						<tabular halign="center">
							<row>
								<cell><var name="$ans3b" width="10" /></cell>
								<cell><m> + c_1 = </m></cell>
								<cell><var name="$ans3a" width="10" /></cell>
								<cell><m> + c_2</m></cell>
							</row>
						</tabular>
					</p>

					<p>
						<em>Don't forget the absolute value on the left antiderivative.</em>
					</p>

					<p>
						<xref ref="sov-step-3" text="title" />. Combine constants as far as possible and use <m>c</m> for the final combined constant.
					</p>

					<p>
						<tabular>
							<col halign="right"/>
							<row>
								<cell>
									<m>y(x) = </m> <var name="$ans" width="10" />
								</cell>
							</row>
						</tabular>
					</p>

				</statement>

			</webwork>

			<hint>
				<p>
					Use the property <m>e^{A + B} = e^{A} \cdot e^{B}</m> to obtain the final combined constant. 
				</p>
			</hint>

		</exercise>

	</exercisegroup>

